# Review sidecars are never part of the published package. NOTE: npm's
# README* auto-include OVERRIDES this ignore for README.md.comments.jsonl
# (verified npm 10/11) — the real guards are the gitignore (CI publishes from
# a clean checkout) and the pre-tag `npm pack` inspection in the release
# skill. This line still covers sidecars swept in via other paths.
*.comments.jsonl

# README screenshots are for the GitHub/npm pages, referenced by absolute
# raw.githubusercontent URLs — no need to ship the bytes in the tarball.
docs/screenshots/
